  "descriptions": [
    {
      "descrType": "Overview",
      "description": "The SPYDER (Surface-to-air PYthon and DERby) is an Israeli ground-based air defense system developed by Rafael Advanced Defense Systems and Israel Aerospace Industries. The system fires the Python-5 infrared-homing and Derby active-radar-homing air-to-air missiles in the surface-to-air role, providing flexible air defense against aircraft and unmanned aerial vehicles. SPYDER is available in multiple variants including short-range (SR), medium-range (MR), extended-range (ER), and long-range (LR) configurations, with the all-in-one variant integrating radar, command/control, and launcher systems on a single mobile vehicle. The system has been in production since 2005 and is operated by multiple nations including India, Singapore, Czech Republic, Vietnam, and others.",
      "shortDescription": "Israeli ground-based air defense system firing Python-5 and Derby missiles with multiple range variants.",
      "classification": "U"
    },
    {
      "descrType": "Design",
      "description": "The SPYDER system combines integrated radar, command post, and launcher platforms in a modular architecture enabling rapid deployment. The SPYDER-SR variant uses inclined, rotatable launchers with the EL/M-2106 ATAR radar for detection ranges of 70-110 km against fighter-sized targets. The SPYDER-MR variant employs vertical launch systems and the EL/M-2084 MMR radar capable of detecting targets at 250 km with processing capacity for 1,200 targets simultaneously. The Python-5 missile provides infrared guidance with a 40 km range, while the Derby missile offers active radar homing with an 80 km range. Mobile platforms enable deployment on standard 8x8 or 6x6 truck configurations for worldwide rapid deployment.",
      "shortDescription": "Modular ground-based air defense with rotatable or vertical launchers, integrated radar systems, and dual-missile armament.",
      "classification": "U"
    }
  ],
